<para id="fs-idp48302032">(d) Ca, H, K, N, Si</para>
<para id="fs-idp251836720">(e) Cl, Cs, Ge, H, Sr</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idp31566784">
<problem id="fs-idp186425376">
<para id="fs-idp65374912">Which atoms can bond to sulfur so as to produce a positive partial charge on the sulfur atom?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp77775472">
<para id="fs-idm121823728">N, O, F, and Cl</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idp9464672">
<problem id="fs-idp10397696">
<para id="fs-idp36762400">Which is the most polar bond?</para>
<para id="fs-idm10175808">(a) C–C</para>
<para id="fs-idp66031184">(b) C–H</para>
<para id="fs-idp291761760">(c) N–H</para>
<para id="fs-idp167633952">(d) O–H</para>
