</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idp173506592">
<problem id="fs-idm53807920">
<para id="fs-idm79569728">Identify the more polar bond in each of the following pairs of bonds:</para>
<para id="fs-idp20525952">(a) HF or HCl</para>
<para id="fs-idp84064688">(b) NO or CO</para>
<para id="fs-idp64282448">(c) SH or OH</para>
<para id="fs-idp65680032">(d) PCl or SCl</para>
<para id="fs-idp183486032">(e) CH or NH</para>
<para id="fs-idp254054736">(f) SO or PO</para>
<para id="fs-idp58442352">(g) CN or NN</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm12999776">
<para id="fs-idm3310160">(a) HF; (b) CO; (c) OH; (d) PCl; (e) NH; (f) PO; (g) CN</para>
